## Acceptance criteria

* Support Agent can consume sanitized recent message threads from Django internal APIs via shared `DjangoClient`
* Fetched data remains tenant/store scoped through existing service JWT conventions
* Caller-provided context is merged deterministically with fetched Django context
* Fetch failure does not crash the support run; safe `django_fetch_failed` warnings are returned
* No raw PII is introduced into logs, warnings, fixtures, prompts, or outputs
* Step 9.1 approval policy, Step 9.2 refusal behavior, Step 9.3 prompt-injection guardrails, and Step 9.4 schema validation are preserved
* Focused deterministic tests cover successful fetch, fetch failure fallback, and caller-context merge without external services
* No real external side effects, real LLM API calls, Django DB access from agents, or Prestia-specific hardcoding
* Steps 9.6–9.8 are not implemented in this step
* `docs/phases/step-9.5.md` documents the implementation
